/*****************************************************************************
    Referencing unidentified blocks in code
*****************************************************************************/
You do not have to declare blocks that you reference in code, as the JIT parser will look for any field names it cannot identify in the set of searchable blocks (it looks in the current registry search list).
#search+ music artist year album genre;
#load phone;
#print 10 artist;
#stop;
/***************************************************************************
	groupTwo extracts only those playlist records from phone that are by
    A.R. Rahman or in the album Journey
***************************************************************************/
<:groupTwo phone><@*+ artist="A.R. Rahman" | album=Journey;>
#print 4 groupTwo;
<restrict song artist/>
/***************************************************************************
	filteredGroup filters groupTwo by including only the attributes from
    the restrict mask defined above. Thus the records of filteredGroup
    only have song and artist attributes.
***************************************************************************/
<:filteredGroup filterBy=restrict groupTwo/>
#print filteredGroup;
#;
